## Specs-D7 Backend Flat Mode Project Resolution
**Status:** implemented
**Module:** `backend/src/forge/mod.rs`
**Tags:** stack:backend
**Depends on:** Specs-G1

### Problem

Frontend calls `/api/forge/specs/{project}` with project name (e.g., `auto-forge`), but flat mode stores the document under key `"."` in `SpecsStore.projects`.

### Solution

`SpecsStore.get_or_default()` falls back to flat mode document when project key not found:

```rust
pub fn get_or_default(&mut self, project: &str) -> &mut SpecsDocument {
    if !self.projects.contains_key(project) {
        if let Some(ref flat) = self.flat_mode_project {
            if let Some(doc) = self.projects.get(flat).cloned() {
                return self.projects.entry(project.to_string()).insert(doc);
            }
        }
        let doc = self.default_specs(project);
        self.save_ad_format(&doc, project);
        self.projects.insert(project.to_string(), doc);
    }
    // ...existing section merge logic...
}
```

### Requirements

- `manifest.at` `project` field MUST be `"."` to match API path semantics
- Any mismatch causes backend to serve default empty docs and overwrite `.ad` files


